<br>
This is supposed to make wizards wanted in groups?<br>
<br>
ROFL<br>
<br>
Well I am a level 60 wizard and I can say.. thank god I don't ever need to get in a group ever again...<br>
<br>
Is this spell useful?  Seems like it might be on big raids if it works..  but will is cause people to want wizards in a group?  Not likely...<br>
<br>
He thinks wizards are balanced in power?  So the fact that a rogue can out damage a wizard going full nuke is balanced?  Now the wizard sits down and meds for 20 min to med and the rogue keeps backstabbing the whole time..<br>
<br>
This makes me so mad I am speechless..<br>
<br>
Verant declares WAR on their customers...  hundreds of of wizards are casualties... news at 11...<br>
<br>
Thank god for AO and DAOC...<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ucrossxbones.showPublicProfile?language=EN>crossXbones</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/15/01 11:56:54 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm10.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=429.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: This is what we have been waiting for?</span><hr size=1> Ok, as a new line of spells...I have to admit this is pretty cool. But as a fix for grouping?  NOT<br>
<br>
Problems with idea are numerous. First this only helps the high level game.  That narrows you down somewhat. Then it is only useful in zones where mobs are gating away and summoning everyone to their deaths.  (Chardok , PoG come to mind ...). I only go to these type of zones on Guild Raids.  Problem with this is that I DO NOT HAVE A PROBLEM GETTING A GROUP ON RAIDS WITH GUILD MEMBERS.  My problem is going to a busy place like KC, where I have been LFG for three freaking days.   This will not help me get a group but in some very specific raids  so this != to a fix for grouping. Call it what you will, its a great line for wizards on raids, but please don't call it a grouping fix. <p><center><a href="http://www.deliveranceforever.com"><img src="http://www.vinfi.com/izra.jpg"></a></center><br>
"Elves are born of the spring, but there is one born in the dead of winter, his heart beats not blood but ice" -- Felwithe Elder<br>
48th Wizard </p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ucodegurux.showPublicProfile?language=EN>CodeguruX</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/15/01 3:05:12 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm10.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=429.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: This is what we have been waiting for?</span><hr size=1> Arg! I wish I was level 50+ so I could know<br>
what people are talking about. I speak to wizard<br>
after wizard and people on the boards are like<br>
