anyway. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ujarnin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Jarnin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/15/01 3:10:42 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm10.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=429.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.interofficenetworks.com/demo/doh/sigpic.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: This is what we have been waiting for?</span><hr size=1> I hate to point this out, but stopping an NPC from gating isn't a hard thing to do (unless it's an epic/boss MoB). All I have to do is nuke with an interrupt spell, and that does the trick.<br>
<br>
In otherwords, When the MoB is low on HP, I wait to see that it's going to gate and cast shock of lightning. That spell, even though it's a level 12 spell, will interrupt the MoBs casting 80% of the time.<br>
<br>
Why would the gating thing be our new group enhancement? It makes no sense. It's almost as useful as givng Wizards a bash skill.<br>
<br>
This is not an improvement. This is not a Group Fix. This is a smack in the face with yet another worthless spell that will likely not get used except on high level encounters.<br>
<br>
The fact that we get these spells at level 51 again shows us that VI thinks we're fine how we are. Personally I think this really isn't our Class Enhancement. I think the fact that we can now use our Kunark Evacs anywhere on Norrath is a bigger Improvement. Now I can be the taxi as discribed by the vision, serving more locations than Mc Donalds.<br>
<br>
/shout DING DING! Anybody need a Lift?<br>
<br>
 <p><center><br>Jarnin Fisheermann<Br><b>Disciple of Hate<Br><b>Rallos Zek</b><Br></b><Br>Grand Master Fisherman<Br>Master Brewer<Br>Master Chef<Br>Master of Begging</center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/usarxosthesorcerer.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Sarxos the Sorcerer</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/15/01 8:15:43 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm10.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=429.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.eqiceni.co.uk/members/sarxossmall1.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: This is what we have been waiting for?</span><hr size=1> I think most people have realised that this isnt a bad line of spells, in fact its quite good for a wizard, but it doesnt help us where we have been screaming for help - getting groups.<br>
<br>
If you are fighting a mob that is going to gate and you cannot stun or draught of jiva it to interrupt it, you are most likely raiding anyway in the likes of WW, DN, PoG. That means I am with my guild, not getting a pickup group.<br>
<br>
Also this line is also very stealth, people will very soon stop remembering that this dragon gates, because the wizard will stop it gating but no-one will be thinking this. Again, people will not be seeing what the wizard is doing.<br>
<br>
They are trying to fix the high-end game only obviously. But the fact is, people see wizards as crap because we dont visibly give them anything (ie, they dont see a nice pretty buff icon) and therefore people are dumb enough not to consider wizards for groups. The problem isnt with the wizard, its with the 98% of morons who play EQ and only think buffs.<br>
<br>
